The final dataset schema belongs to the final table created by the pipeline, which is stored inside A schema for the final dataset: cardinals_pipeline.db, specifically the table: fact_ticket_interest_weather

# Schema
-The table below integrates ticket engagement data with weather forecasts to create a dataset.
| Column                 | Type    | Description                            |
| ---------------------- | ------- | -------------------------------------- |
| snapshot_date          | DATE    | Date when ticket activity was recorded |
| game_date              | DATE    | Date of the game                       |
| days_before_game       | INTEGER | Days between snapshot and game         |
| unique_page_clicks     | INTEGER | Ticket page engagement                 |
| unique_tickets_sold    | INTEGER | Tickets sold                           |
| forecast_temp          | FLOAT   | Forecasted temperature                 |
| forecast_precip_prob   | FLOAT   | Probability of precipitation           |
| forecast_condition     | TEXT    | Human-readable weather condition       |
| forecast_snapshot_date | DATE    | Date the forecast was retrieved        |

# Why this Schema Works
- analysis of engagement by days_before_game
- compare engagement against precipitation forecasts
- study how forecasts change as the game approaches 
